# Sloane V2 — Build Context (condensed from SLOANE_V2_CLAUDE_CODE.md)

Single working spec for V2 build. Source of truth is SLOANE_V2_CLAUDE_CODE.md;
this is the navigational digest for future sessions. Read the full doc before
implementing any section.

> **Post-V2 note:** web-app work was layered on after V2 (Ask Sloane web chat,
> chat-forward home + UI redesign, agent-targeted reply nudges + optional reply
> forwarding, migration 016). That work is **not** in this digest or the V2 spec —
> see the "Web app (post-V2)" and "Inbound email threading (4)" sections of CLAUDE.md.

## Mission

Virtual TC for small brokerages (2–10 agents) replacing Gmail + shared Sheet +
DocuSign chaos. Primary user: broker-owner who is also a producing agent. Every
feature decision: "does it make her Monday morning less overwhelming?" Default
to simple; surface complexity only when asked.

## Stack — Do Not Recreate

- Backend: FastAPI + httpx (no ORM, direct Supabase REST)
- Frontend: React 18 + TS + Vite + Tailwind + Zustand + Axios + RHF + Zod
- DB: Supabase Postgres + RLS, every query scoped by `brokerage_id`
- Auth: Supabase Auth, `brokerage_id` in JWT `app_metadata` (single source of truth)
- AI: Anthropic claude-sonnet-4 (native doc blocks; strict JSON; empty on uncertainty)
- Messaging: Twilio (WhatsApp + SMS, signed webhooks)
- Email: SendGrid
- Storage: Supabase buckets (`contracts`, `knowledge-docs`, `listing-packets`, `compliance-docs`)
- Voice: OpenAI Whisper
- Market data: Rentcast

Live-tested today: auth, onboarding, contract PDF extraction, transactions,
WhatsApp text+voice, knowledge base, doc generation, deadlines, compliance
review (AI + structural), comps, scheduling, MLS listing prep.

## Non-Negotiable Security

- No API keys in frontend, ever
- `service_role` server-side only
- Every DB query scoped by `brokerage_id`
- Compliance review NEVER autonomous (no flag, no setting, no path)
- Confirmation gates required for: email send, document send, compliance
  decision, appointment booking, listing push, deadline party notification
- Extracted fields never hallucinated — empty string on uncertainty
- `TWILIO_SKIP_VALIDATION` must be false in production

## Migration Strategy

Numbered files continuing from 001–005 (and currently shipped 006–015). Apply
in order. Never modify existing migrations. Every new table:
- `id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY`
- `brokerage_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES brokerages(id) ON DELETE CASCADE`
  (or scoped via parent transaction)
- `created_at timestamptz DEFAULT now()`
- RLS policy scoped by `brokerage_id`

## Build Sections

### 1. Remove Adoption Blockers

**1A. WhatsApp/SMS inbound PDF/image processing**
- Extend Twilio inbound handler: detect `MediaUrl0` + `MediaContentType0`
- Download w/ Twilio Basic Auth (urls expire fast)
- PDF → existing extraction pipeline; image (jpg/png/heic/heif) → Claude image block
- HEIC/HEIF → JPEG via Pillow
- Store extracted fields in `pending_whatsapp_transactions`
  (brokerage_id, whatsapp_contact_id, extracted_fields JSONB, pdf_storage_url, expires_at = now+2h)
- YES/yep/correct → create transaction; corrections → parse + re-summarize
- 15MB cap; duplicate-address warning; unknown sender → register first

**1B. Per-agent style profiles**
- Migration 006: `ALTER TABLE knowledge_rules ADD COLUMN agent_id uuid REFERENCES agents(id)`
  + index `(brokerage_id, agent_id)`. agent_id NULL = brokerage-wide.
- `agents` table if missing (id, brokerage_id, name, email, phone, whatsapp_number, sms_number, license_number)
- `get_confirmed_knowledge_rules(brokerage_id, agent_id=None)`: fetch brokerage rules always;
  if agent_id, also fetch agent-specific; agent rules take precedence on conflict
- Wire agent_id into all doc-gen + email-draft calls (known from WA contact + web session)
- Web UI: "My Style" tab — upload sample → propose → confirm (same UX as brokerage KB)
- Admin: view (not edit) per-agent profiles; delete allowed

**1C. SMS fallback channel**
- Rename/extend `whatsapp_contacts` → `agent_channels`
  (id, brokerage_id, agent_id, channel CHECK('whatsapp'|'sms'), phone_number, display_name,
   UNIQUE(brokerage_id, phone_number, channel))
- Migrate existing whatsapp_contacts with channel='whatsapp'
- New route `POST /api/v1/sms/inbound`: same signature validation + contact lookup
  + same tool-use loop, text-only (no voice memo, no media on SMS this phase)
- Reply via `messages.create(from_=SMS_NUMBER, ...)`
- Onboarding: admin chooses whatsapp/sms/both per agent
- New env: `TWILIO_SMS_FROM` (standard Twilio number, not WhatsApp sender)

### 2. Broker Compliance File

**2A. Compliance Checklist Engine (migration 007)**
Tables:
- `compliance_templates` (brokerage_id NULL=system default, state, transaction_type
  CHECK('buy_side'|'list_side'|'dual_agency'|'lease'), name, is_system_default)
- `compliance_template_items` (template_id, sort_order, label, description, required,
  document_required, notes)
- `transaction_checklist_items` (transaction_id, template_item_id NULL=manual, label,
  required, document_required, status CHECK('pending'|'complete'|'waived'|'not_applicable'),
  completed_at, completed_by, document_url, waiver_note, sort_order)

Seed system defaults: buy-side 16 items + list-side 16 items (see full doc lines 333–369).

Endpoints:
- `GET/POST/PUT /api/v1/compliance-templates`
- `GET /api/v1/transactions/:id/checklist`
- `POST /api/v1/transactions/:id/checklist/items` (manual add)
- `PATCH /api/v1/transactions/:id/checklist/items/:item_id` (complete/waive/upload)
- `DELETE /api/v1/transactions/:id/checklist/items/:item_id` (manual items only)

Auto-instantiate on transaction creation; pick best template (brokerage custom > system default,
matching state). Compute `checklist_pct` server-side; include in list responses.

WhatsApp: "what's missing for 123 Main?" → list pending required only;
"mark inspection complete" → confirm-gated update.

**2B. Broker Review Queue**
- `GET /api/v1/broker/review-queue` returns 4 categories: compliance_attention,
  closing_soon_incomplete (<5d AND <80% checklist), overdue_deadlines (past due_date),
  stale_transactions (no activity 7+ days — needs `last_activity_at` on transactions)
- Each row: tx id, address, buyer, closing date, stage, checklist_pct, agent, one-line reason
- UI: 4 collapsible sections, count badges, inline review-note textarea, 5min auto-refresh
- Dashboard banner: "🚨 N items need your review" when count > 0
- Admin role only

### 3. Workflow Task Templates (migration 008)

Tables:
- `workflow_templates` (brokerage_id NULL=system default, name, state, transaction_type, is_system_default)
- `workflow_steps` (template_id, sort_order, label, description,
  trigger_type CHECK('stage_entry'|'days_before_deadline'|'days_after_stage'|'manual'),
  trigger_stage, trigger_deadline_label, trigger_days,
  assigned_to_role CHECK('agent'|'admin'|'buyer'|'seller'|'lender'|'title'),
  due_offset_days)
- `transaction_tasks` (transaction_id, step_id NULL=manual, label, description, due_date,
  assigned_to_role, status CHECK('pending'|'complete'|'skipped'), completed_at, completed_by, skip_reason)

Seed buy-side default workflow (see full doc lines 561–588). Hook generator into:
- Transaction creation (stage_entry: under_contract)
- Stage PATCH
- Deadline reminder run (days_before_deadline)

WhatsApp tool `get_pending_tasks`: group by urgency (overdue/today/this_week/upcoming).
"Mark inspection ordered" → confirm-gated complete.

UI: Tasks panel on transaction detail; overdue badge on transaction list.

### 4. Inbound Email Reply Threading (migration 009)

DNS: `reply.heysloane.io` MX → `mx.sendgrid.net`. Configure Inbound Parse → `POST /api/v1/email/inbound`.

Outbound emails: `Reply-To: tx-{transaction_id}@reply.heysloane.io`

Table `transaction_emails` (transaction_id, direction CHECK('outbound'|'inbound'),
sender_email, sender_name, recipient_emails[], subject, body_text, body_html,
sendgrid_message_id, read, read_at, read_by, received_at).

`POST /api/v1/email/inbound` (public, validates SendGrid signature via `SENDGRID_WEBHOOK_KEY`):
extract transaction_id from `to`, verify brokerage ownership, store, WhatsApp-nudge admin
(preview truncated 120 chars).

All existing SendGrid sends log to `transaction_emails` (direction='outbound', sendgrid_message_id).

UI: Communications tab — chronological interleave, unread highlight, expand-to-read,
Reply opens draft via doc-gen flow (human reviews + confirms — never auto-reply).

Endpoints: `GET /api/v1/transactions/:id/emails`, `POST .../emails/read`.

### 5. EMD Tracking (migration 010)

`ALTER TABLE transactions ADD COLUMN`:
- emd_amount numeric, emd_due_date date, emd_received boolean DEFAULT false,
  emd_received_date date, emd_receipt_document_url text,
  emd_held_by CHECK('title'|'brokerage'|'escrow'|'other'), emd_notes text

Contract extraction wires `earnest_money` → `emd_amount`; if contract has EMD due date, extract.

Review queue: add `emd_overdue` category (top priority, 🔴).

UI: EMD card on transaction detail (amount, due, held_by, received). Mark Received:
date picker + optional receipt upload → `compliance-docs` bucket.

WhatsApp: query status, mark received (confirm-gated).

**Constraint**: receipt tracking only. NO calculations, NO disbursements, NO trust math.
UI label: "EMD Receipt Tracking."

### 6. AI Disclosure + Party Consent (migration 011)

Table `party_consents` (transaction_id, party_role, email, consented_at, ip_address,
user_agent, consent_method DEFAULT 'email_link').

`ALTER TABLE brokerages ADD`:
- ai_disclosure_enabled boolean DEFAULT true
- ai_disclosure_text text DEFAULT (standard disclosure paragraph)

Disclosure footer: when enabled, append to every outbound email (small, muted, below sig).

Optional consent link: HMAC-signed `GET /api/v1/consent/{transaction_id}/{party_role}?token=...`
using `CONSENT_SECRET`. Verify → record in party_consents → simple HTML thank-you.
Gated by per-brokerage `request_ai_consent` (default false).

UI: Compliance Settings — toggle disclosure, edit text (with legal warning), toggle
explicit consent, per-tx consent status panel.

### 7. Broker Reporting

All metrics from existing transaction data. No external BI.

`GET /api/v1/reports/broker-summary?period=month|quarter|ytd` returns:
- pipeline (active_transactions, active_volume, by_stage, closing_this_month + volume)
- at_risk (overdue_deadlines, closing_soon_incomplete, stale_transactions)
- production (closed_count, closed_volume, avg_days_to_close, agent_breakdown[])
- compliance (avg_checklist_completion_at_close, open_compliance_items_total)

Add `closed_at` to transactions if missing; set on stage → 'closed'.
`avg_days_to_close` = closed_at - created_at.

`GET /api/v1/reports/transactions-export?period=...` → CSV of closed transactions.

UI: Reports nav page, three sections (Pipeline / Production / Compliance Health) +
recharts bar chart. Period selector: This Month / This Quarter / YTD. No drill-down,
no custom date range in V1.

### 8. DocuSign Integration

**Prerequisite**: DocuSign developer account + integration key (client ID) required
before this section starts. Production needs DocuSign partner review.

OAuth 2.0 Auth Code grant. Table `docusign_tokens` (brokerage_id, access_token,
refresh_token, expires_at, docusign_account_id, docusign_user_id).

Brokerage settings: "Connect DocuSign" → OAuth → store tokens → "Connected."

`POST /api/v1/transactions/:id/docusign/send` body: { document_url, signers[], email_subject, message }.

`POST /api/v1/docusign/webhook` (Connect): on 'completed', fetch signed doc URL, store
in `signed_contract_url` (or contract_pdf_url), add transaction note.

UI: Signatures card — "Send for Signature" pre-fills from party contacts, confirm-gated,
status indicator (Draft/Sent/Partial/Completed/Declined), link to signed doc.

**Scoping constraint**: NOT a forms library. DocuSign sends documents Sloane already has
(extracted contracts, generated correspondence). NOT generating state association forms
(see Hard Limit 1).

## Hard Limits — Document in BLOCKERS.md, Do Not Engineer Around

1. **State association forms** — Dotloop/zipForm have NAR + state assoc licensing.
   Sloane can extract/track/sign, but cannot distribute forms. 6–18 month legal process.

2. **MLS write APIs** — ~580 MLSs, each needs separate data access agreement + creds
   (sometimes RESO Web API cert). Pursue per beachhead market only; `mls_provider` seam
   is ready.

3. **Google/Microsoft Calendar OAuth** — Google verification 4–12 weeks (possibly security
   assessment). Submit verification now; `calendar_provider` seam is ready.

4. **WhatsApp Business API production approval** — Twilio Sandbox today. META approval
   can be delayed/rejected for real estate. Apply now; SMS fallback (1C) is the
   production-ready channel meanwhile.

5. **AI reliability in compliance review** — LLMs miss/false-flag findings. Human gate
   is load-bearing — NEVER autonomous. Add `confidence` field (high/med/low self-report);
   surface low-confidence with distinct treatment. UI text: "checklist aid, not legal
   determination."

6. **SOC 2 / NPI handling** — Enterprise-adjacent brokerages won't sign without SOC 2
   Type II. 6–12 month process. Interim: Privacy Policy + DPA, reference Supabase's
   SOC 2 + ISO 27001, configurable retention setting (default 7 years).

## Deployment Checklist (per feature)

- [ ] RLS policies on all new tables, scoped by brokerage_id
- [ ] JWT auth on all new endpoints except designated public webhooks
- [ ] Webhook signature validation (Twilio, SendGrid, DocuSign)
- [ ] New env vars in `.env.example` w/ descriptions
- [ ] Migrations numbered sequentially, tested in order on clean Supabase
- [ ] Storage buckets created with access policies
- [ ] BLOCKERS.md updated if blocked by a Hard Limit
- [ ] DEPLOYMENT.md updated for new DNS/platform/external requirements

## Framing — Always

User is a broker-owner running a 6-agent shop, also producing. Never had a TC.
Comparing Sloane to her current chaos (Gmail + Sheet + DocuSign), not to SkySlope.
Every feature should make Monday morning easier. If she has to think about it,
simplify it. If she has to maintain a second system, she'll abandon it.

